h6.Summary
The target URL of the *Create pull request* link in the JIRA issue details doesn't account for the capitalisation of the Bitbucket team name. As a result, the user is redirected to a screen with the incorrect branch selected as source.

h6.Steps to reproduce
# create a JIRA issue in an instance linked to a Bitbucket account with capital letters in it;
# create two branches linked to that JIRA issue;
# commit to branch 1;
# commit to branch 2;
# in the JIRA issue, open the _Branches_ dialog and click *Create pull request* for branch 1.

*Expected result:* Bitbucket screen for creating a pull request from branch 1 is displayed.
*Actual result:* Bitbucket screen is displayed, with the branch most recently committed to selected as source - regardless of the branch selected in JIRA. 

h6.Cause
The *Create pull request* JIRA link ignores the team name capitalisation. The link target URL is: https://bitbucket.org/team/repository/pull-request/new?source=team%2Frepository%3A%3Abranch-1. Bitbucket isn't able to associate it with the correct branch, and so the user is redirected to https://bitbucket.org/Team/repository/pull-request/new which uses the default source branch.

In the branch list in Bitbucket, the *Create pull request* is formatted correctly: https://bitbucket.org/Team/repository/pull-request/new?source=Team/repository%3A%3Abranch-1&event_source=branch_list

DVCS appears to continue synchronizing a repo but its actually silently failing, which is reflected in the JIRA logs. 

At present DVCS is displaying more changesets than are actually present:
{quote}
Synchronizing: 8338 changesets
{quote}

