I created a test issue and then associated a commit to it from Github.  The commit is shown as occurring 7 hours in the past in JIRA.

When pushing a commit with a message like:
{quote}
{{TEST-1 #resolve This is a comment made at the same time the issue is resolved.}}
{quote}
The issue will be resolved but no comment will be added. According to [the documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AOD/Processing+JIRA+issues+with+commit+messages#ProcessingJIRAissueswithcommitmessages-Commands], this is a something that should be allowed.

The workaround is to include an explicit {{#comment}} directive, e.g.
{quote}
{{TEST-1 #resolve #comment This is a comment made at the same time the issue is resolved.}}
{quote}

